article.headline: Jackson St. 62, Alabama A&amp,M 53
article.story: HUNTSVILLE, Ala. -- Jeremy Caldwell scored 14 points to lead Jackson State to a 62-53 win over Alabama A&M on Monday night. The win snapped a seven-game losing streak for the Tigers (2-12, 1-1 Southwest Athletic Conference). Caldwell also finished with 10 rebounds, and Darrion Griffin added 13 points. The Bulldogs (3-7, 1-1) were paced by Trant Simpson, who scored 14. Jonathan Inman chipped in with 10 points and five rebounds. After holding a 53-50 lead with 3 minutes remaining in the game, the Tigers finished the game with a 9-3 run for the final margin. Jackson State outrebounded Alabama A&M 49-42. The Bulldogs shot 32.2 percent from the field (19-for-59), and was just 1 of 14 from 3-point range.
